#fba324" graphic_icon="diamond"][x_feature_box title="Feature List Item" title_color="" text="This is an Feature List Item that is part of an Feature List. Notice the connector between the three graphics to show that they are related." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="3px" connector_style="dotted" connector_color="#fba324" graphic_icon="bicycle"][x_feature_box title="Feature List Item" title_color="" text="This is an Feature List Item that is part of an Feature List. Notice the connector between the three graphics to show that they are related." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="60px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="3px" connector_style="dotted" connector_color="#fba324" graphic_icon="envelope-o"][/x_feature_list][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 40px auto -50px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tree_care_industry.png" alt="Tree and Shrub Pruning-Trimming Toronto- Tree Care Industry Member" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="top" info_trigger="hover" info_content=""][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/isa.jpg" alt="Tree and Shrub Pruning-Trimming Toronto- ISA Member" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="top" info_trigger="hover" info_content="" class="image"][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/landscape_ontario.png" alt="Tree and Shrub Pruning-Trimming Toronto- Landscape Ontario Association Member" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="top" info_trigger="hover" info_content=""][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#f7f9d2" id="section-services" class="center-text " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 70px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="man"]How to Prune Trees?[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="20px"][x_text class="justify-text "]In spring, you may have to do a lot of pruning to remove the excessive growth of shrub or trees in your yard. Your localÂ <a href="https://www.almileytree.com/arborist-toronto/">Toronto arborist</a> would recommend pruning trees in winter but there are always a few exceptions. In fact, itâ€™s always better if you can prune the trees a few months before they start to grow. Once the trees begin budding or blooming in spring, pruning can be such a tiresome task.[/x_text][x_gap size="20px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_feature_list animation_offset="50" animation_delay_initial="0" animation_delay_between="170"][x_feature_box title="Take Time" title_color="" text="Take time to assess the tree. Look at its current height and shape and envision how you would like it to appear once youâ€™re done with pruning. Identify the main branches of the tree. These are the branches that make up the treeâ€™s skeleton. Avoid removing these branches as you could slow down their growth." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#095c31" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="clock-o" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Signs of Damager" title_color="" text="Identify branches that show signs of damage. This includes branches that are broken or look weathered. Get rid of these damaged branches first. Keeping them will prevent healthy branches from getting adequate water and nutrients since they continue consuming them." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#634f40" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="warning" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Pick and Choose" title_color="" text="Look out for branches that cross each other and remove them. These branches prevent air circulation and may hinder light from reaching all parts of the tree. Any branches that are too close together should be removed as they can contribute to the growth of fungus and insect infestation. Get rid of branches that are growing inward as they could cause clutter." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#65ac22" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="eye" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Eliminate Branches Blocking Walkways" title_color="" text="Eliminate any branches that are blocking the walkways or coming into contact with telephone wires, the roof or close to your house. Any branches that are causing some type of obstruction need to be pruned." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#879314" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="leaf" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Pruning for Neater and Pleasant Shape" title_color="" text="Pruning can also be done to give the tree a neater and more pleasant shape. If you feel a few branches stick out and give the tree a funny look, donâ€™t be afraid to make a few cuts. Prune only as much as you need too. A little cut can make a big difference so donâ€™t remove more than 25% of the treeâ€™s branches." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#879314" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="tree" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Don't Pruning Too Much" title_color="" text="Tree branches are important for its survival. Pruning too much can expose the tree to dangerous fungus and insects because it compromises its protection system. If you remove all the branches, it can cause stress for the plant and it will take a long while for the tree to recover." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="150px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#879314" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="exclamation-circle" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][/x_feature_list][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#ffffff" id="section-whyUs" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 25px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="center-text "]Tree Pruning in Spring Season[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][x_text]Pruning trees in Spring has some serious potential risks. If not properly done, the trees may be left with cuts which put them at an increased risk of insect infestation or diseases. But thereâ€™s a way that tree pruning can be done safely in spring. You just have to ensure that you donâ€™t remove more than 10% of the tree branches. The idea here is <strong>to do minimal pruning</strong> to enhance the aesthetics of the tree.[/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 10px auto 10px auto; padding: 10px 0px 0p20px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  class="left-text " style="padding: 1px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_feature_list][x_feature_box title="Feature List Item" title_color="" text="This is an Feature List Item that is part of an Feature List. Notice the connector between the three graphics to show that they are related." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="0px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image=""][x_feature_box title="Feature List Item" title_color="" text="This is an Feature List Item that is part of an Feature List. Notice the connector between the three graphics to show that they are related." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="0px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image=""][x_feature_box title="Feature List Item" title_color="" text="This is an Feature List Item that is part of an Feature List. Notice the connector between the three graphics to show that they are related." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="0px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image=""][/x_feature_list][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/How-to-Prune-Trees-in-Spring.jpg" alt="" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="top" info_trigger="hover" info_content=""][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 1px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_custom_headline level="h3" looks_like="h5" accent="false" class="center-text "]Which types of trees are best to prune in spring?[/x_custom_headline][x_feature_list][x_feature_box title="Feature List Item" title_color="" text="This is an Feature List Item that is part of an Feature List. Notice the connector between the three graphics to show that they are related." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="0px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image=""][x_feature_box title="Feature List Item" title_color="" text="This is an Feature List Item that is part of an Feature List. Notice the connector between the three graphics to show that they are related." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="0px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image=""][x_feature_box title="Feature List Item" title_color="" text="This is an Feature List Item that is part of an Feature List. Notice the connector between the three graphics to show that they are related." text_color="" graphic="image" graphic_size="0px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#ffffff" graphic_bg_color="#2ecc71" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="#272727" graphic_image=""][/x_feature_list][x_text]There are certain tree species that thrive when pruned in spring. If you have <strong>apricot trees, dogwood trees, lilac or magnolia,</strong> you can prune them once theyâ€™ve finished blooming.

Some trees like <strong>maple and walnut</strong> will ooze sap when pruned which can be so messy to work with. We would recommend trimming them after they have all their leaves for the season. There are certain <strong>types of trees that shouldnâ€™t be pruned</strong> or trimmed in spring. Remember that pruning can sometimes leave the trees vulnerable to diseases and insect attacks. For instance, avoid pruning oak trees, elm trees and Sycamores in spring. If you are unsure of whether to prune the trees in your yard, work with your <strong><a title="Almiley Tree Service" href="https://www.almileytree.com/">arborist</a></strong> to determine whatâ€™s best and how to get it done safely. Al Miley &amp; Associates - expert <a title="Tree and Shrub Pruning / Trimming Toronto" href="https://www.almileytree.com/tree-and-shrub-pruning-trimming-toronto/">Tree and Shrub Pruning / Trimming Toronto</a>.[/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section parallax="false" bg_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Green_back_03.jpg" bg_color="#449322" class="call_to_action" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 45px 0px 45px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_text class="nomargin" style="margin: 0!important;"]<h4 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">Get A Free Quote</span></h4>[/x_text][gravityform id="4" title="false" description="false" ajax="true"][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_gap size="30px"][x_text class="left-text "]Our experts are on call to assist you in every way. The moment you reach out, we will customize a service that fits your specific needs and budget. Donâ€™t hesitate to call us for the most reliable pruning services in Toronto.[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_gap size="50px"][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/tree-pruning.jpg" alt="Tree and Shrub Pruning-Trimming Toronto" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="right" info_trigger="hover" info_content="" id="free_label" style="width: 100%; margin: -49px auto 0 auto; min-height: 180px;"][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#f7f9d2" id="section-services" class="center-text " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 70px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="man"]Tips and Warning on Tree Pruning[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="20px"][x_text class="justify-text "]In spring, you may have to do a lot of pruning to remove the excessive growth of shrub or trees in your yard. Your localÂ Toronto arborist would recommend pruning trees in winter but there are always a few exceptions. In fact, itâ€™s always better if you can prune the trees a few months before they start to grow. Once the trees begin budding or blooming in spring, pruning can be such a tiresome task.[/x_text][x_gap size="20px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_feature_list animation_offset="50" animation_delay_initial="0" animation_delay_between="300"][x_feature_box title="Remove Dead Wood" title_color="" text="You can remove dead or dying wood at any time throughout the different seasons.

