" text_color="" graphic="numbers" graphic_size="70px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#634f40" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0" connector_style="dotted" connector_color="#3a771b" graphic_animation="fadeInDown" connector_animation="fadeInDown"][x_feature_box title="Use pruning shears" title_color="" text="Use pruning shears to cut off small branches

" text_color="" graphic="numbers" graphic_size="70px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#65ac22" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0" connector_style="dotted" connector_color="#3a771b" graphic_animation="fadeInDown" connector_animation="fadeInDown"][x_feature_box title="Use Lopping Shears" title_color="" text="Use lopping shears for medium size (1â€™â€™+diameter) branches and for branches larger than 2â€™â€™ diameter, use a tree saw.

" text_color="" graphic="numbers" graphic_size="70px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#879314" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0" connector_style="dotted" connector_color="#3a771b" graphic_animation="fadeInDown" connector_animation="fadeInDown"][x_feature_box title="Avoid Hedge Shears" title_color="" text="Avoid using hedge shears when pruning trees as they can cause damage

" text_color="" graphic="numbers" graphic_size="70px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#879314" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0" connector_style="dotted" connector_color="#3a771b" graphic_animation="fadeInDown" connector_animation="fadeInDown"][x_feature_box title="Dip Tools in Isopropyl Alcohol" title_color="" text="Dip the cutting tools in isopropyl alcohol when pruning different trees to prevent the spread of disease from tree to tree.

" text_color="" graphic="numbers" graphic_size="70px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#879314" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0" connector_style="dotted" connector_color="#3a771b" graphic_animation="fadeInDown" connector_animation="fadeInDown"][x_feature_box title="Wear Protective Clothing" title_color="" text="Wear protective clothing (a long sleeved shirt, gloved and safety goggles) when pruning trees.

" text_color="" graphic="numbers" graphic_size="70px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#879314" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="middle" side_graphic_spacing="20px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0" connector_style="dotted" connector_color="#3a771b" graphic_animation="fadeInDown" connector_animation="fadeInDown"][x_feature_box title="Do not Top" title_color="" text="Do not top (pruning trees for height) shade trees. Topping a shade tree can cause serious harm to the branch structure and overall strength of the tree.


